dspace-development.title: Symplectic Elements: "Claimed" Items Missing in Queue

comments.body:
Directly querying the MSSQL Server database is necessary in order to begin diagnosing this:

```mssql
USE elements;

GO
SELECT * FROM dbo.OBJECT_tblObject WHERE ID=173746;
GO
```

Comparing a single claimed and a single unclaimed publication, there only seems to be a difference in the `EverApproved` field:

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1443986/161274510-5993213e-e3f5-45b7-801f-11465a0e61aa.png)
For reference, those records with a non-NULL `User_ID` field persist attributes for users within the application.

Currently, as my own user, I cannot search for any recommended publications which have not been claimed at all:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/9de894ef-122f-4daf-bdae-1302178f27ea)

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/dccbb427-5bbe-4e33-b835-339d885e9aa1)

Searching for publications and linking my user account to one did not seem to prevent users from being able to search for the record by title:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/cfd5357d-916b-4e09-a897-29c21adf275b)

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/c46f5532-8e53-416b-9d27-ef3b157b1d93)

Inspecting the database records, the one distinguishing factor is the difference in modification dates:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/371f5762-20d1-43e8-9764-4433fd867c88)

This would coincide with a date earlier than that of the last search index regeneration:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/66bd3313-c2f5-4222-8b0a-8f904abbea10)
I am going to proceed by attempting to generate the search index for today.

dspace-development.title: Symplectic Elements: Searching queues seem frozen

comments.body:
Rebooting the server has not resolved this issue as anticipated, and I have provided the following update to Symplectic Support:

```
Dear Jeff,

I apologize for the delay, the reboot did not successfully resolve this issue.

I did, however, find the following log entries for the "Manage Data Sources":
2022-04-01 12:00:23 [arXiv synchroniser]: 100 postponed Fetch work items reactivated.

2022-04-01 12:00:23 [arXiv synchroniser]: New work found. Waking up...

2022-04-01 12:00:23 [arXiv synchroniser]: Processing priority 10 fetch for a batch of 100 records...

2022-04-01 12:00:25 [arXiv synchroniser]: arXiv made an invalid response.

2022-04-01 12:00:25 [arXiv synchroniser]: Fetch batch errored. Retry postponed until after 4/2/2022 12:00:25 PM.

2022-04-01 12:00:25 [arXiv synchroniser]: Since the arXiv synchroniser was last restarted, 9952 work items have been automatically enqueued, 400 reactivated, 100 successfully processed, 0 discarded and 4 postponed. If no logging has appeared since the last such message, the ongoing work has resulted in no data changes.

2022-04-01 12:00:25 [arXiv synchroniser]: There is currently no more work to do.

2022-04-01 14:29:44 [arXiv synchroniser]: arXiv synchroniser stopped.

2022-04-01 14:54:29: Maximum ETL extract batch size: 20Mb.

2022-04-01 14:54:30 [arXiv synchroniser]: arXiv synchroniser started.

2022-04-01 14:54:30 [arXiv synchroniser]: Object Search queue deactivated.

2022-04-01 14:54:30 [arXiv synchroniser]: Change Check queue deactivated.

2022-04-01 14:54:30 [arXiv synchroniser]: Harvest queue deactivated.

2022-04-01 14:54:30 [arXiv synchroniser]: Push queue deactivated.

2022-04-01 14:54:30 [arXiv synchroniser]: There is currently no more work to do.




Might there be some way of determining whether or not these errors are related to the logged "arXiv made an invalid response" event?




If this is unrelated, please let me know how it might be best to continue trying to diagnose this.

Thank you,
James 
```
